00:29:34,647 --> 00:29:37,650
Something he would like. Hmm.

559
00:29:38,651 --> 00:29:39,944
This is pretty.

560
00:29:42,655 --> 00:29:43,865
I choose this one.

561
00:29:50,079 --> 00:29:51,122
This one.

562
00:29:54,709 --> 00:29:58,171
Dear Yudai,

563
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:05,720
Thank you for today. I had fun!

564
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:10,141
If you are free tomorrow (Day Nine),
will you go for lunch with me?

565
00:30:10,225 --> 00:30:15,605
I will be waiting for you
at 12:00 p.m. at Place Masséna.

566
00:30:34,749 --> 00:30:38,586
Aru sent a letter to Maho in the end.

567
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:42,173
It might have turned out differently
if it was before Maho's date with Yudai.

568
00:30:42,257 --> 00:30:44,008
- Exactly.
- It's the timing.

569
00:30:44,092 --> 00:30:45,051
Ever since then,

570
00:30:45,134 --> 00:30:46,386
<i>she's been crazy about him.</i>

571
00:30:46,469 --> 00:30:48,137
<i>- She's crazy about him.</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

572
00:30:48,221 --> 00:30:51,641
Mimi's tactic of not going
to Margaux is amazing, isn't it?

573
00:30:51,724 --> 00:30:56,604
If she receives a letter from Aru,

574
00:30:56,688 --> 00:31:00,942
she has no choice but to decline.

575
00:31:01,025 --> 00:31:04,070
- She doesn't want to run into him either.
- No, she doesn't.

576
00:31:04,153 --> 00:31:07,907
Mimi doesn't talk to people
about the things that bothered her.

577
00:31:07,991 --> 00:31:12,036
She’s the type of person
who solves things on her own.

578
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:15,415
So, right now,
the way she's coping with her situation

579
00:31:15,498 --> 00:31:17,792
is by not going to Margaux
or reading letters.

580
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:21,754
If Atsushi is willing to meet with her,
then there’s no need to go.

581
00:31:21,838 --> 00:31:24,549
It's like she's declared
that she’s chosen Atsushi.

582
00:31:24,632 --> 00:31:25,758
- I see.
- Yeah.

583
00:31:25,842 --> 00:31:29,178
That's some strategy.
She'd rule the world in a different time.

584
00:31:29,679 --> 00:31:31,222
- That's true.
- Right?

585
00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:33,600
<i>Kanaka and Sho painting pictures was nice.</i>

586
00:31:33,683 --> 00:31:35,935
<i>They were painting. It looked fun.</i>

587
00:31:36,019 --> 00:31:38,646
And Sho went to buy flowers.

588
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:41,274
<i>He's usually very cool,</i>
<i>but at the florist's,</i>

589
00:31:41,357 --> 00:31:42,567
he was like a cute child.

590
00:31:42,650 --> 00:31:43,568
You're right.

591
00:31:43,651 --> 00:31:47,238
"Cool, beautiful.
Very, very beautiful flower."

592
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:51,743
Will they start going out on Day Eight?

593
00:31:51,826 --> 00:31:53,661
What will he say to her?

594
00:31:53,745 --> 00:31:55,538
Will he just say that he likes her,

595
00:31:55,622 --> 00:31:57,916
or will he ask her to go out with him?

596
00:31:57,999 --> 00:32:01,920
That's true.
That aspect of the show is vague.

597
00:32:02,003 --> 00:32:04,172
They could start going out on Day Eight

598
00:32:04,255 --> 00:32:08,176
and be a couple on Days Nine and Ten.

599
00:32:08,259 --> 00:32:10,845
- They'd go, "We're in a relationship!"
- Yeah.

600
00:32:10,929 --> 00:32:12,972
They might send letters to everyone.

601
00:32:13,056 --> 00:32:14,849
- Like, "We're going out."
- Yeah.

602
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:16,935
No one needs that announcement.

603
00:32:17,435 --> 00:32:19,938
Tohko went to buy clothes.

604
00:32:20,021 --> 00:32:21,773
<i>Aru kind of stirred her up.</i>

605
00:32:21,856 --> 00:32:23,483
<i>What Aru wanted to say</i>

606
00:32:23,566 --> 00:32:25,818
was that Yudai likes fashion.

607
00:32:25,902 --> 00:32:28,780
He wanted to tell her
to keep that in mind.

608
00:32:28,863 --> 00:32:31,616
But he mentioned
that Maho and Yudai's fashion matched.

609
00:32:31,699 --> 00:32:33,534
When Tohko heard that, she was like…

610
00:32:35,203 --> 00:32:39,123
<i>Even the act of buying clothes</i>
<i>on her own to meet someone</i>

611
00:32:39,207 --> 00:32:43,002
feels like growth for Tohko, doesn’t it?

612
00:32:43,086 --> 00:32:47,298
It's things like this
that help you gradually become an adult.

613
00:32:47,382 --> 00:32:49,342
Tohko was open about herself.

614
00:32:49,425 --> 00:32:53,930
By saying that she's never been
in a relationship and stuff,

615
00:32:54,013 --> 00:32:56,265
she was making things easier for herself.

616
00:32:56,349 --> 00:33:00,228
She was making Yudai match her
since this was her first experience.

617
00:33:00,311 --> 00:33:03,815
But now, she’s stretching herself
and trying to match up to him.

618
00:33:03,898 --> 00:33:05,400
To get him to like her.

619
00:33:05,483 --> 00:33:07,860
Tohko learned to stretch herself in Nice.

620
00:33:08,903 --> 00:33:11,197
- How nice.
- She'll come back a new Tohko.

621
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:12,699
Come back? Where?

622
00:33:12,782 --> 00:33:15,076
She'll be different
when she's back in Japan.

623
00:33:15,159 --> 00:33:17,078
I'd love to say, "You're so different!"

624
00:33:17,578 --> 00:33:19,122
"Are you really Tohko?"

625
00:33:20,081 --> 00:33:21,749
She won't look different.

626
00:33:35,930 --> 00:33:37,306
We've climbed up high.

627
00:33:38,266 --> 00:33:40,685
- We climbed another mountain.
- Yeah.

628
00:33:40,768 --> 00:33:43,688
- We've climbed so many mountains.
- We're above the clouds.

629
00:33:43,771 --> 00:33:46,441
- Whoa.
- Wow.

630
00:33:50,153 --> 00:33:52,071
- Wow.
- Wow!

631
00:33:52,155 --> 00:33:53,364
This is amazing!

632
00:33:53,448 --> 00:33:55,074
- They run so cute.
- They're running.

633
00:33:55,158 --> 00:33:57,118
- The two are adorable.
- Yeah.

634
00:33:57,201 --> 00:33:58,786
Wow.

635
00:33:59,579 --> 00:34:00,621
Whoa.

636
00:34:03,458 --> 00:34:04,667
This is stunning.

637
00:34:04,751 --> 00:34:06,586
- That's Èze, right?
- Yeah.

638
00:34:07,086 --> 00:34:08,254
We've come so high up.

639
00:34:20,016 --> 00:34:23,102
You know, up until now,

640
00:34:23,186 --> 00:34:26,355
I've been saying

641
00:34:26,439 --> 00:34:28,691
that you're really pretty.

642
00:34:29,192 --> 00:34:35,281
But I never told you
why I think you're so great.

643
00:34:35,990 --> 00:34:37,533
I never explained that.

644
00:34:38,034 --> 00:34:40,369
- So, can I say everything?
- Yeah.

645
00:34:40,453 --> 00:34:42,830
Well, this will be a bit long.

646
00:34:43,331 --> 00:34:45,458
But I'll say it all.

647
00:34:49,212 --> 00:34:55,968
KANAKA, 25, BRAND PRODUCER

648
00:34:56,052 --> 00:34:56,886
Hey.

649
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:58,930
You look beautiful.

650
00:34:59,013 --> 00:35:00,723
SHO, 22, UNIVERSITY STUDENT AND MODEL

651
00:35:00,807 --> 00:35:03,518
- Here.
- Wow! What is this?

652
00:35:04,227 --> 00:35:06,479
I bought flowers for you.

653
00:35:06,562 --> 00:35:07,980
It's huge!

654
00:35:08,064 --> 00:35:10,650
I've never received flowers
when it’s not my birthday.

655
00:35:10,733 --> 00:35:12,443
I just wanted to give it to you.

656
00:35:12,527 --> 00:35:15,154
Thank you. I'm so happy.

657
00:35:15,238 --> 00:35:16,739
- So cool!
- So cool!

658
00:35:16,823 --> 00:35:17,824
What's with these two?

659
00:35:17,907 --> 00:35:19,200
What is with these two?

660
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:22,662
It's pretty heavy,
so you can leave it at the hotel.

661
00:35:22,745 --> 00:35:23,788
- Really?
- Yeah.

662
00:35:24,288 --> 00:35:27,125
- I'll quickly go put it in my room.
- Sure.

663
00:35:27,208 --> 00:35:28,376
- Wait for me.
- Okay.

664
00:35:33,464 --> 00:35:35,258
Kept you a-waiting.

665
00:35:35,341 --> 00:35:37,468
I made you wait. Sorry.

666
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:40,179
"Kept you a-waiting."

667
00:35:41,013 --> 00:35:44,767
- He's so different.
- "Kept you a-waiting. I made you wait."

668
00:35:44,851 --> 00:35:46,894
Oh! Did you get a new coat?

669
00:35:47,562 --> 00:35:48,521
- Right?
- Maybe?

670
00:35:48,604 --> 00:35:50,022
- What?
- Maybe I brought this.

671
00:35:50,106 --> 00:35:51,190
- Oh?
- Yeah.

672
00:35:51,274 --> 00:35:52,525
- Let's go.
- Looks warm.

673
00:35:52,608 --> 00:35:53,484
- This way?
- Yeah.

674
00:35:53,568 --> 00:35:54,610
You picked a place?

675
00:35:54,694 --> 00:35:55,528
- Yeah.
- Oh?

676
00:35:55,611 --> 00:35:57,071
- Of course.
- Wow.

677
00:35:58,114 --> 00:35:58,990
Are you cold?

678
00:36:00,241 --> 00:36:01,117
Here.

679
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:03,369
Which way is it?

680
00:36:04,078 --> 00:36:04,912
Like this?

681
00:36:04,996 --> 00:36:06,038
MIMI, 20, PART-TIME WORKER

682
00:36:06,122 --> 00:36:07,874
ATSUSHI, 30,
FORMER NATIONAL WATER POLO MEMBER

683
00:36:08,457 --> 00:36:11,043
- It looks good on you.
- It smells nice.

684
00:36:14,672 --> 00:36:17,133
- Is it warmer this way?
- Yeah. It's warm.

685
00:36:17,633 --> 00:36:20,261
- He put something on her again.
- He gives her every cloth.

686
00:36:20,344 --> 00:36:22,096
He's doing it again today.

687
00:36:22,180 --> 00:36:23,764
Atsushi, the cloth-giver.

688
00:36:24,932 --> 00:36:26,267
It's going to end soon.

689
00:36:27,268 --> 00:36:28,561
It's over so fast.

690
00:36:29,437 --> 00:36:32,607
It's Day Nine tomorrow. Time flies.

691
00:36:36,402 --> 00:36:38,070
- What is it?
- What?

692
00:36:38,154 --> 00:36:40,823
- How is it going?
- What?

693
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:43,284
Have you decided

694
00:36:43,784 --> 00:36:47,538
who you want to meet on the last day?

695
00:36:56,255 --> 00:37:02,220
YUDAI, 24, MODEL AND ACTOR

696
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:07,725
- The white bench.
- It's Yudai.

697
00:37:07,808 --> 00:37:09,352
What will he tell her?

698
00:37:10,478 --> 00:37:11,729
It was on Day Three.

699
00:37:12,939 --> 00:37:14,732
- You sent me a letter.
- Yeah.

700
00:37:14,815 --> 00:37:17,526
I thought you just randomly
put it in my mailbox.

701
00:37:18,152 --> 00:37:19,862
- But I was genuinely happy.
- Right.

702
00:37:20,363 --> 00:37:22,490
I was wondering
what kind of person you were.

703
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:24,200
And I met you that same night.

704
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:27,078
Yudai and I were there first.

705
00:37:27,578 --> 00:37:29,747
And then Tohko and you came in.

706
00:37:30,248 --> 00:37:34,877
I was thinking, "I hope she's Nanami,"
before you introduced yourself.

707
00:37:35,378 --> 00:37:38,381
And then I was like, "Oh, she <i>is </i>Nanami!"

708
00:37:38,881 --> 00:37:41,550
"I get to see her tomorrow. I'm excited."

709
00:37:42,051 --> 00:37:43,052
The next day,

710
00:37:43,552 --> 00:37:46,597
I saw you waiting at Place Masséna.

711
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:49,308
I thought, "She's so pretty!"

712
00:37:50,309 --> 00:37:51,269
Thank you.

713
00:37:51,352 --> 00:37:54,522
It was raining, but you were there.

714
00:37:54,605 --> 00:37:56,774
I wasn't sure if you'd really come.

715
00:37:57,275 --> 00:37:59,652
So, I thought, "She's here!"

716
00:38:00,569 --> 00:38:02,238
We went to have lunch together.

717
00:38:02,738 --> 00:38:05,866
- It was the best meal I'd had until then.
- Yes, it was.

718
00:38:06,367 --> 00:38:07,451
- That lunch.
- Yeah.

719
00:38:07,535 --> 00:38:08,369
And I thought,

720
00:38:09,161 --> 00:38:11,539
"It's because
I'm eating this with Nanami."

721
00:38:12,456 --> 00:38:14,542
We went to look at bags after that.

722
00:38:15,751 --> 00:38:17,003
You picked one out for me.

723
00:38:17,503 --> 00:38:21,173
It was exactly the one
I’d wanted for so long.

724
00:38:21,674 --> 00:38:26,178
I've been carrying it with me ever since.

725
00:38:26,262 --> 00:38:27,805
It's like a good luck charm.

726
00:38:27,888 --> 00:38:29,765
Then, we went to the beach.

727
00:38:29,849 --> 00:38:33,811
And you were just shining.

728
00:38:34,437 --> 00:38:35,438
Right.

729
00:38:35,521 --> 00:38:39,692
The light from the sunset
was shining on you.

730
00:38:39,775 --> 00:38:43,738
I thought, "She's so beautiful."

731
00:38:44,238 --> 00:38:49,076
At that moment, I thought,
"I want to be with her till the last day."

732
00:38:49,660 --> 00:38:54,582
You got the Wish Letter
from Yudai that day.

733
00:38:54,665 --> 00:38:58,586
I was devastated
and couldn't get any words out.

734
00:38:58,669 --> 00:39:00,588
But I also received a Wish Letter.

735
00:39:01,088 --> 00:39:02,423
I went to the vineyard.

736
00:39:02,923 --> 00:39:04,258
It was beautiful.

737
00:39:04,759 --> 00:39:08,220
I kept thinking things like,
"Nanami won't see this scenery,"

738
00:39:08,721 --> 00:39:11,807
and, "She won't eat this local dish."

739
00:39:11,891 --> 00:39:13,684
I had fun with Tohko.

740
00:39:14,393 --> 00:39:16,771
But I still thought,
"I wish I could show Nanami."

741
00:39:17,271 --> 00:39:20,316
I was waiting for you
at Margaux that night.

742
00:39:20,816 --> 00:39:23,361
I was all like, "Oh, man…"

743
00:39:24,153 --> 00:39:25,446
But you came.

744
00:39:25,529 --> 00:39:27,448
I was like, "Yes!"

745
00:39:28,115 --> 00:39:29,367
We went skiing.

746
00:39:29,450 --> 00:39:32,620
I thought, "I'll stay by Nanami's side."

747
00:39:33,537 --> 00:39:35,873
I wanted you to help me.

748
00:39:36,540 --> 00:39:39,919
I had so much fun today too.

749
00:39:40,419 --> 00:39:43,422
Since the day we met,

750
00:39:43,964 --> 00:39:48,594
I’ve only been thinking
about you during this whole trip.

751
00:39:50,805 --> 00:39:52,139
You're always smiling,

752
00:39:53,432 --> 00:39:56,769
and you're always kind to others.

753
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:06,112
Someone like that
probably isn't kind to themselves.

754
00:40:08,823 --> 00:40:12,701
I saw that part… of you too.

755
00:40:13,786 --> 00:40:18,040
I love you very much

756
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:21,669
as a person and as a woman.

757
00:40:29,718 --> 00:40:30,928
Thank you.

758
00:40:37,059 --> 00:40:40,855
- I hope I can meet you again in Japan.
- Yeah.

759
00:40:43,607 --> 00:40:44,442
Yes.

760
00:40:45,985 --> 00:40:49,864
You're pretty at each and every second.

761
00:40:49,947 --> 00:40:51,699
Thank you.

762
00:40:52,324 --> 00:40:54,076
It's a bit embarrassing.

763
00:40:55,619 --> 00:40:56,662
The whole time.

764
00:40:57,580 --> 00:41:02,501
So, that was my trip in Nice.

765
00:41:05,629 --> 00:41:08,799
This old woman here almost cried.

766
00:41:08,883 --> 00:41:11,051
- Did you?
- But this was really nice.

767
00:41:11,135 --> 00:41:15,389
He said, "Someone who's kind to others
probably isn't kind to themselves."

768
00:41:15,473 --> 00:41:17,933
- That was wonderful.
- A lovely expression.

769
00:41:18,017 --> 00:41:20,186
I imagine it was like that for Nanami.

770
00:41:20,269 --> 00:41:23,105
- She acted strong.
- That's right.

771
00:41:23,189 --> 00:41:25,316
He told her he wanted to see her in Japan.

772
00:41:25,399 --> 00:41:28,569
He's the first one
to say something like this.

773
00:41:28,652 --> 00:41:32,740
She must be happy that he talked about
when they go back to Japan.

774
00:41:32,823 --> 00:41:34,283
Like it doesn't end here.

775
00:41:34,366 --> 00:41:35,451
You're right.

776
00:41:35,534 --> 00:41:38,537
Isn't it nice when humans fall in love?

777
00:41:40,039 --> 00:41:41,457
What are you, a monster?

778
00:41:42,166 --> 00:41:44,084
I love romance between human beings.

779
00:41:45,711 --> 00:41:46,670
I love it.

780
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:51,467
This looks delicious.

781
00:41:52,259 --> 00:41:53,636
Wow.

782
00:41:54,470 --> 00:41:55,387
Merci.

783
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:59,308
- Wow!
- This looks amazing.

784
00:41:59,808 --> 00:42:00,768
Let's eat.

